HEADWORD: Dehors
<hw>De*hors"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prep.</pos> <ety>[F.,
outside.]</ety> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>Out of; without; foreign to; out
of the agreement, record, will, or other instrument.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dehors</ent>⟦br⟧
